CHANGELOG.md:745:- Added depth-2 groove-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0082): `tests/test_groove_engine.py` now includes `GrooveEngineEndToEndTests`, which drives `groove_for_section(...)`, entrainment tempo nudging, IOI adjustment, meter-policy overlay, JSON-safe groove metadata, and `build_scene_from_score(...)` through one deterministic tracker scene. `tests/test_test_groove_engine_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Production fixes keep entrainment from stripping registered groove shape by replacing the existing immutable profile rather than rebuilding a partial one, and tracker scene compilation now falls back to a resolved profile's lane offsets before using the global default. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4551 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:747:- Added depth-2 governor integration end-to-end test coverage (frac-0081): `tests/test_governor_integration.py` now includes `TestGovernorIntegrationEndToEnd` which drives the resource governor lifecycle through nominal, emergency spike, recovery, CPU-only, and master-bus-dead paths. `tests/test_governor_integration_depth.py` pins the file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/resource_governor.py` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:749:- Added depth-2 generative-scores end-to-end test coverage (frac-0080): `tests/test_generative_scores.py` now includes `GenerativeScoresEndToEndTests`, which drives mood score generation, narrative-event score generation, memory-fragment recall, repertoire hints, hook metadata, JSON-safe payloads, and `score_to_frequencies(...)` through the public score pipeline. `tests/test_test_generative_scores_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generative_scores.py` behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4541 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:751:- Added depth-2 generation request end-to-end test coverage (frac-0079): `tests/test_generation_request.py` now includes `TestGenerationRequestEndToEnd`, which drives the `GenerationRequest` data structure through the full lifecycle of request creation, rejection of invalid types and boundaries, hash stability independent of backend/model string choices, hash divergence on generation parameter changes, and immutability. `tests/test_generation_request_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2. Existing per-function assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/request.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:753:- Added depth-2 generation health end-to-end test coverage (frac-0078): `tests/test_generation_health.py` now includes `GenerationHealthEndToEndTests`, which drives the IDyOM KL-divergence audit through real temporary LTM files, rolling history persistence, collapse alert output, JSON-safe `AuditReport.to_dict()` round-trips, no-auto-rollback hash preservation, and the config-driven `_main()` path via `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG`. `tests/test_test_generation_health_depth.py` pins the health test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation-health assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/health.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4517 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:755:- Added depth-2 generation composer-hook end-to-end test coverage (frac-0077): `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` now includes `GenerationComposerHookEndToEndTests`, which drives the public composer-hook surface (`_should_queue_now`, `build_generation_request`, `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD`) plus the duet-composer integration `_post_song_generation_hook` through the full gate -> build -> enqueue cycle. The end-to-end scenarios cover a happy-path enqueue with a real builder via a thin `_ConditionerAdapter` that asserts the queued payload equals `build_generation_request(...)`, idempotency key matches `request_hash`, and the request hash is a 64-char content-addressed digest; gate-denial paths for low daily budget at the `MIN_DAILY_BUDGET_REMAINING_USD` floor, sampler-dominating antipatterns, working-ambience low arc payoff, and rate-limited recent enqueue under `MIN_GENERATION_INTERVAL_SECONDS`, all confirming `_post_song_generation_hook` returns `None` with no queue traffic; deterministic-builder identity for equal inputs and distinct hashes/seeds for changed mode or arc phase; and a JSON-safe round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)` on the built request and the queued payload. `tests/test_test_generation_composer_hook_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_composer_hook.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function composer-hook assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/composer_hook.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4514 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:757:- Added depth-2 generation client protocol end-to-end test coverage (frac-0076): `tests/test_generation_client_protocol.py` now includes `GenerationClientProtocolEndToEndTests`, which drives a typed `GenerationRequest` through a structural `GenerationClient`, typed `GenerationResult` output, JSON-safe `result_summary`, `cost_per_second`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` success/failure diagnostics. `tests/test_test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins the protocol test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` behavior remains unchanged because the protocol helpers already produced meaningful output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4508 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:759:- Added depth-2 generation cache end-to-end test coverage (frac-0075): `tests/test_generation_cache.py` now includes `GenerationCacheEndToEndTests`, which drives the public `GenerationCache` API through the full miss → put → hit → replace cycle (asserting content-addressed filenames, suffix preservation, accessed-at LRU updates, and in-place byte replacement), the queue/storage `set`/`get` aliases sharing a single on-disk entry with `put`/`lookup`, a JSON-safe index round-trip via `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, a multi-entry restart that recovers surviving entries while pruning a payload deleted out-of-band, and a combined count + size LRU cap where an explicit lookup keeps the oldest entry warm and forces eviction of the middle entry. `tests/test_test_generation_cache_depth.py` pins `tests/test_generation_cache.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function generation cache assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/cache.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4504 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:761:- Added depth-2 garden watcher end-to-end test coverage (frac-0074): `tests/test_garden_watcher.py` now includes `GardenWatcherEndToEndTests`, which drives the public garden watcher path through deterministic brightness/time snapshot building, JSON-safe operator summary generation, and atomic runtime-state persistence. `my-claw/tools/senseweave/garden_watcher.py` now exposes `build_garden_state`, `summarize_garden_state`, and `write_current_garden_state`, while `update_garden_state` delegates through the deterministic builder so existing callers keep the same one-path behavior. `tests/test_test_garden_watcher_depth.py` pins the garden watcher test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4498 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:763:- Added depth-2 gallery-x11-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0073): `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` now includes coverage for `load_playlist`, `render_art`, `render_overlay`, and `init_pygame_display` using mocked data and a dummy SDL driver. A scoping bug in `my-claw/tools/gallery/gallery_x11.py` where overlay rendering logic was inadvertently placed inside `init_pygame_display` was fixed. A depth gate ensures `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` is pinned at fractal depth >= 2. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:765:- Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:767:- Added depth-2 federation-discovery end-to-end test coverage (frac-0071): `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` now ships a `FederationDiscoveryEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `discover_peers`, `save_peer_registry`, `load_peer_registry`, and `merge_peer_registry` surface end-to-end through fakes for `tailscale status --json` and the `/federation/v1/identity` endpoint. The end-to-end scenarios cover the full discover → save → load → re-scan → merge → save cycle (verifying meaningful `PeerInfo` fields, JSON-safe registry payloads, `to_dict`/`from_dict` round-trips, online/offline flag flips for vanished peers, `first_seen` preservation for returning peers, and online-on-arrival semantics for new peers), multi-IP peer fall-through where a later IP responds after an earlier IP refuses, and an empty rescan that marks every previously seen peer offline while preserving its identity and timestamps. `tests/test_test_federation_discovery_depth.py` pins `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class, loading `sdp.fractal.classify_depth` via `importlib.util` to remain deterministic against the local classifier. Existing function-level federation discovery assertions and the production `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4483 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:769:- Added depth-2 dashboard-generator coverage and the simplest Observatory-backed class path (frac-0070): `tests/test_dashboard_generator.py` now includes `DashboardGeneratorEndToEndTests`, which builds temporary SDP, Observatory, and pet-state inputs and verifies `generate_dashboard(...)` renders meaningful service, pipeline, pet class/level, event, and timestamp output without scripts. `tests/test_test_dashboard_generator_depth.py` pins the dashboard-generator test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. `my-claw/tools/dashboard_generator.py` now derives pet class overrides from Observatory `agent_skills` by mapping known skill categories to existing dashboard classes, accumulating score-weighted sample counts, selecting one dominant class per agent, and passing those overrides through `generate_dashboard(obs_db=...)`; missing or unreadable Observatory databases still return no class overrides. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4479 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:819:- Added depth-2 hook schema rewriter (frac-0044): `rewrite_hook.py` is now an importable module with a frozen `HookRewriteResult` dataclass plus typed helpers `apply_field_renames`, `migrate_file`, `apply_hook_rewrites`, and `main`, sourced from a canonical `HOOK_FIELD_RENAMES` table (`("hook_type", "hook_class")`, `("rhythm_cell", "rhythm")`) and `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` listing the five SenseWeave files the original one-shot script wrote to. The previous body of unconditional regex/`str.replace` calls — which left an already-migrated tree corrupted with duplicate dataclass fields and a broken `return HookProfile(...)` block when re-run — is replaced by an idempotent rename: `apply_field_renames` is pure string-in/string-out, `migrate_file` only writes when the produced text differs from disk and reports `existed`/`changed`, missing files report `existed=False` without raising, and `apply_hook_rewrites(root)` walks `HOOK_TARGET_FILES` in declared order returning one `HookRewriteResult` per target. `main()` prints a `rewrote`/`unchanged`/`missing` line per result and exits 0; `if __name__ == "__main__"` is preserved. `tests/test_rewrite_hook_depth.py` pins canonical-rename, idempotency, write-on-change, no-op-on-migrated-file, missing-file handling, declared-order tree migration, end-to-end idempotency on a migrated tree, the canonical rename table, and fractal depth >= 2; senseweave hook tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:833:- Added depth-2 entities-domain migration planning (frac-0037): `narrative/migrations/20260502_001347za_add_entities_domain.py` now exposes a frozen `DomainColumnPlan` plus `domain_column_plans()` and `domain_migration_summary()` so the CN-001 migration can report its canonical `entities` / `events` domain-column plan, generated upgrade SQL, reverse downgrade targets, revision id, and default domain in JSON-safe form. `upgrade()` and `downgrade()` now execute through the same plan while preserving the existing `domain TEXT DEFAULT 'shared'` behavior for existing rows, new explicit domain values, and downgrade/re-upgrade. `tests/test_narrative_entities_domain_migration.py` pins the plan, summary, existing SQLite migration behavior, and fractal depth >= 2; narrative entity API and startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:943:- Added a manifest-driven CCS-032 library migration path: `my-claw/tools/sample_library_import.py` now imports single files and directory buckets into `samples/library/`, `senseweave.sample_library.SampleRecord` / `SampleLibrary` now preserve full-record provenance via serialized record storage (including `extras.original_path` and `extras.captured_by`), `tests/test_sample_library_import.py` locks the importer contract, `sample_manifests/anthony-library.toml` captures Anthony's real 101-sample migration plan, and the resulting local library import is kept out of git via `.gitignore`.
