sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1539:my-claw/sdp/prd-songwriter-emsd-completion.md:168:| SWE-020 | Add live performance resource governance for music quality. | MUST | T1 | - CPU, node count, sampler load, capture freshness, self-listener RMS, and master bus health influence degradation rules<br/>- degradation reduces optional voices/samples/grains before interrupting primary form<br/>- tests verify graceful fallback under simulated CPU pressure, stale capture, and dead master bus |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1540:my-claw/sdp/prd-songwriter-emsd-completion.md:170:| SWE-022 | Build repertoire promotion, curation, and archive integration. | MUST | T1 | - completed pieces store score tree summary, ear metrics, audio render reference, source samples, hook text, motif ids, form class, and ending<br/>- strong motifs/forms can be promoted into house repertoire<br/>- archive storage uses the 10TB storage root when available<br/>- tests verify promotion rules, no exact duplicate titles/hooks when alternatives exist, and archive path resolution |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1556:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:92:| CCS-004 | Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary.bootstrap(root)` creates the six subdirectories + `index.sqlite` if missing, idempotent<br/>- documented as the canonical layout in module docstring<br/>- tests verify bootstrap on tmp dir creates all six subdirs and the SQLite file |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1557:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:93:| CCS-005 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord \| None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1558:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:102:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1559:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:105:| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → "warm"; narrow-band high-centroid → "metallic"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → "sustained"; transient_density>3/sec → "percussive"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → "harmonic"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1560:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:106:| CCS-018 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1561:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:107:| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1562:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:112:| CCS-024 | When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py` listens for keyboard/theramini activity via existing state files (`/tmp/midi_keyboard_activity.json`, `/tmp/theramini_state.json`)<br/>- on >5-second sustained play, captures the corresponding window from the appropriate JACK input<br/>- tags include `human_player` (e.g. `anthony` if face_recognition supports it, else `unknown`), `instrument` (`midi_keyboard` / `theramini`), and the inferred key the human played in<br/>- tests verify trigger threshold, source routing, and tag inclusion |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1563:my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md:116:| CCS-028 | Composer post-piece hook: write a sample-usage journal entry per piece (which samples played, what transformations, what arc payoff). | MUST | T1 | - `samples/usage_journal.jsonl` appended one line per piece with `piece_id`, `started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used: list[{sample_id, source, transposition, fx_preset, played_at_row}]`, `arc_payoff`, `clicks`<br/>- journal is durable (fsynced after each line)<br/>- tests verify schema and atomicity |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:1570:my-claw/sdp/prd-synthesis-and-orchestration.md:305:Implement `oscillator.py`. One class that works at every time scale. Parameters: frequency, waveform (sine/saw/triangle/noise/buffer/physical_model), amplitude, envelope (ADSR or arbitrary contour), phase. Modulation inputs: list of other Oscillators that modify this one's frequency, amplitude, or waveform parameters. Output: at audio rate (>20Hz) produces PCM samples (S32_LE, 48kHz). At control rate (0.1-20Hz) produces control values for modulating other oscillators. At form rate (<0.1Hz) produces structural decisions (key change, section boundary, motif selection). Write tests verifying output at multiple time scales, modulation accuracy, and waveform correctness.
