sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9860:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9862:- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9866:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9872:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9879:- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9896:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9921:- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9994:- Added quota-aware graceful degradation for CypherClaw live command routing using `sdp-cli` provider headroom.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9995:- Hardened the managed runner service contract: `cypherclaw-sdp-runner.service` now uses `Restart=always` so clean `sdp-cli run` exits do not strand the queue, while maintenance-gated launcher exits use status `75` and are treated as intentional non-restarting stops.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:9996:- Hardened the managed runner launcher so it auto-exports a sibling `sdp-cli/src` checkout into `PYTHONPATH` when available, keeping the live runner on the checked-out source tree instead of a stale installed package.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10006:- Taught Telegram `/monitor` to prefer the real `sdp-cli monitor --last` snapshot when available, so Telegram now mirrors the live run/phase/timing/quota/risk panel from the terminal monitor instead of a thinner daemon-only summary.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10007:- Expanded Telegram `/monitor` with compact `sdp-cli`-style status lines for completion gate, latest completed run verdict/pair, and live per-agent quota/provider health.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10009:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10010:- Normalized Telegram `/monitor` and `/prd` status buckets with `sdp-cli` so split parents show as `skipped` and live pending/blocked/running counts match the CLI.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10011:- Kept `needs_split` as a first-class queue bucket across Telegram and `sdp-cli` instead of folding it into `pending`, so queue shape remains visible during decomposition.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10012:- Added long-term active-run drift detection and repair for stale open `task_runs`, and taught `/monitor` to surface queue-state drift explicitly when runtime bookkeeping falls out of sync.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10034:- Added 7 orchestrator hooks (pre/post routing, lead, verify, and finalize) for coherence checks.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:10061:- Added artifact-based handoff flow for lead, verify, and clarification phases.
