sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11671:| CCS-023 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11672:| CCS-024 | When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py` listens for keyboard/theramini activity via existing state files (`/tmp/midi_keyboard_activity.json`, `/tmp/theramini_state.json`)<br/>- on >5-second sustained play, captures the corresponding window from the appropriate JACK input<br/>- tags include `human_player` (e.g. `anthony` if face_recognition supports it, else `unknown`), `instrument` (`midi_keyboard` / `theramini`), and the inferred key the human played in<br/>- tests verify trigger threshold, source routing, and tag inclusion |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11673:| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays "atonally" as a texture<br/>- tests verify transposition for known pitch + key combinations, low-confidence pass-through, and edge cases (octave wraps) |
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:11674:| CCS-026 | Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE: dict[str, dict]` mapping mode name to fx args<br/>- solitary: `delay_time=0.6, delay_feedback=0.65, verb_mix=0.45, freeze_amount=0.2, comb_b_amount=0.4`<br/>- companion: `delay_time=0.5, delay_feedback=0.4, verb_mix=0.3, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.15`<br/>- working_ambience: `delay_time=0.3, delay_feedback=0.2, verb_mix=0.15, freeze_amount=0.0, comb_b_amount=0.1`<br/>- evening_reflection: `delay_time=0.7, delay_feedback=0.55, verb_mix=0.5, freeze_amount=0.15, comb_b_amount=0.3`<br/>- storm: `delay_time=0.25, delay_feedback=0.7, verb_mix=0.25, freeze_amount=0.55, comb_b_amount=0.6`<br/>- tests verify each preset, that values are within SynthDef-acceptable ranges, and that `dispatch_sample` correctly applies the preset for the active mode |
