sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26000:- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26002:- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26006:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
sdp/logs/Lead_T-022_20260425T183959Zd_1777178822.log:26012:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
