sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1742:sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:18:**`evict_lru()` delegation**: The new public `evict_lru()` peeks at the oldest entry with `next(iter(self._lru.items()))` (no mutation), then delegates to `on_sampler_free(oldest)` which sends `/b_free`, clears `buffer_id`, and removes the record from `_lru` via `pop`. The method returns the evicted record (or `None` on empty). This fully routes eviction through the free path — no duplicated release logic remains.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1743:sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:20:**`on_sampler_load` integration**: The overflow branch now calls `self.evict_lru()` replacing the old `self._evict_lru()`. OSC call ordering is preserved: `/b_free` is sent by `on_sampler_free` before `on_sampler_load` issues `/b_alloc` and `/b_allocRead`.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1744:sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:28:- **AC1** (`test_on_sampler_load_evicts_lru_via_on_sampler_free_at_default_capacity`): fills loader to default 64-buffer capacity, triggers a 65th load, asserts `on_sampler_free` called exactly once with `records[0]`, asserts OSC order `/b_free` → `/b_alloc` → `/b_allocRead`, asserts `records[0].buffer_id is None` and new buffer assigned. PASS.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1745:sdp/verification/t-001@20260425t183959zd-verify.md:41:- `next(iter(self._lru.items()))` peek-without-pop pattern avoids re-entrancy hazard: `on_sampler_free` is free to mutate `_lru` without the caller having already removed the entry.
