sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1778:sdp/verification/frac-0072-verify.md:24:The three end-to-end tests drive `resolve_harmonic_plan()` through a deterministic live-like keyboard input (MIDI notes 67/71/74, garden `F lydian`, inner `Dm`, sustained pedal), assert `G:lydian` authority resolution, verify that section functions/cadences/progressions/chord-degree triads/harmonic functions/transition intents are fully populated and internally consistent, confirm modulation continuity via `common_tones()` / `pivot_degree()`, align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` output against the resolved plan, assert tension ordering (emergence < bridge, afterglow < bridge), and round-trip the full payload through `ScoreTree.to_json()` / `ScoreTree.from_dict()`.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1779:sdp/verification/frac-0072-verify.md:28:The spec required one deterministic path — not an edge-case matrix — and that is exactly what was implemented. All six section fields (`harmonic_role`, `cadence_type`, `harmonic_function`, `transition_intent`, `groove_state`, `section_progressions`) are exercised. The depth gate (`test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py`) independently classifies the test file at depth >= 2 and checks for the end-to-end class by AST inspection. Startup identity hardening anchors (CLI, standalone, federated, daemon, ASGI) are re-run as regression guards per spec direction.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1780:sdp/verification/frac-0072-verify.md:36:CHANGELOG entry is detailed and accurate; `progress.md` entry is concise and correctly marks the task complete. Commit messages follow the project's `feat(scope): message [frac-NNNN]` convention across all three commits.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1781:sdp/verification/t-011@20260425t183959z-verify.md:12:- `detect_sampler_dominating` uses the 0.6 threshold and correctly escalates from `warning` to `fail` (MUST FIX) after 3 consecutive occurrences using the `sampler_dominating_streak` from the score metadata.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1782:sdp/verification/t-011@20260425t183959z-verify.md:13:- `detect_sampler_silent_quintet_member` implements a mode-weighted threshold over a rolling 50-piece window. The weighting correctly scales with `sampler_density`, significantly lowering the threshold for low-density modes like `working_ambience`.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:1783:sdp/verification/t-011@20260425t183959z-verify.md:29:- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] The parenthetical goal "(so working_ambience never trips it)" is effectively but not absolutely met; a piece history consisting purely of `working_ambience` with exactly zero sampler usage will still trip the detector (threshold 0.007 > 0.0). However, 1 usage in 50 pieces is sufficient to pass (0.02 > 0.007), which satisfies the intent of being extremely lenient for low-density modes.
