sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:2124:sdp/verification/t-017@20260425t183959z-verify.md:12:The implementation accurately follows the requested formula: `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)`. The `count_sampler_events` function in `sampler_scheduler.py` correctly applies this math and clamps the result to `[0, total_phrases]`. `duet_composer.py` correctly integrates this logic, reading the density from mode-based defaults or score metadata, and recording the resulting plan (count and phrase indices) back into the score metadata.
